comments.body:
@rhatdan yeah if we can get a network-based subuid/subgid that would work, though I imagine that's going to require kernel-level changes so ideally we'd also have a shorter-term solution.

I understand the limitations of a single-uid mode, but given that only some subset of images require multi-uid support, it seems that single-uid is a reasonable use case to support. It can be gated behind an opt-in flag and accompanied by a use-at-your-own-risk warning message so no one is caught unaware.

Anyways this is sort of diverging from the original issue, which is already resolved. Should we create another issue to continue the discussion? I think there are a few bullet points to discuss (e.g. skip lchowns when when images are pulled in single-uid mode, network-based subuid/subgid, etc).
